\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Thereon also rode noble knights and stout men-at-arms,[Pg 2]\~and these you could follow with the eye by their glistening armour, as they wound over hill and dale, mile after mile, with shining spears and shields and fluttering pennons, and anon a trumpet or two sounding the same keen note as that which rang out dreadfully on those bloody fields of France}}